BUG: Compiler doesn't validate that branches with payloads require bindings.

Currently `| result |>` is accepted when `result { value: i32 }` has a payload.
The shape checker should require either:
  - `| result r |>` (bind to r)
  - `| result _ |>` (explicit discard)

This is the same class of bug as metatype branches requiring bindings.
See: shape_checker.zig or flow_checker.zig
